<subSubSection id="3FC9650DAD5DFFC1FF53FCD08BBFFBC6" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="776C3686AD5DFFC1FF53FCD08BBFFBC6" blockId="3.[136,1452,842,1625]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">
The heterogeneous nature of 
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FE16FCD188B1FCBA" box="[461,482,843,868]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">T.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FDFAFCD08BDBFCBA" box="[545,648,842,868]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">Alpestria</emphasis>
was mentioned elsewhere, with a more detailed discussion (
<bibRefCitation id="13424B77AD5DFFC1FAF3FCD689B5FC56" author="Stepanek, J. &amp; Kirschner, J. &amp; Jarolimova, V. &amp; Kirschnerova, L." pageId="3" pageNumber="298" pagination="537 - 564" refId="ref3815" refString="Stepanek, J., Kirschner, J., Jarolimova, V. &amp; Kirschnerova, L. (2011) Taraxacum nigricans, T. alpestre and allies in the Taraxacum sect. Alpestria: taxonomy, geography and conservation status. Preslia 83: 537 - 564." type="journal article" year="2011">
Štěpánek 
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FA4CFCD189F6FC56" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="13424B77AD5DFFC1FF2BFCEA8B7EFC56" author="Stepanek, J. &amp; Kirschner, J." box="[240,557,878,907]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" refId="ref3779" refString="Stepanek, J. &amp; Kirschner, J. (2022) A hotspot of endemism: Oreophytic Taraxacum species (Compositae, Crepidinae) in the mountains of Bulgaria. Phytotaxa [submitted]." type="book" year="2022">Štěpánek &amp; Kirschner 2022</bibRefCitation>
). There are several species groups characterized morphologically, e.g. the group of 
<taxonomicName id="B0D34D05AD5DFFC1FF73FC098A53FC72" authority="(Tausch 1821: 564) Candolle (1838: 148)" authorityName="Candolle" authorityPageNumber="148" authorityYear="1838" baseAuthorityName="Tausch" baseAuthorityPageNumber="564" baseAuthorityYear="1821" box="[168,768,914,941]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpestre">
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FF73FC09884DFC72" box="[168,286,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">T. alpestre</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="13424B77AD5DFFC1FEF5FC0888A8FC73" author="Tausch, I. F." box="[302,507,914,941]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" pagination="557 - 570" refId="ref4121" refString="Tausch, I. F. (1821) Beschreibungen neuer Pflanzen aus dem Riesengebirge. Flora oder Botanische Zeitung 4 (2): 557 - 570." type="journal article" year="1821">Tausch 1821: 564</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="13424B77AD5DFFC1FDD0FC088A53FC72" author="Candolle, A. P. de" box="[523,768,914,940]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" refId="ref3343" refString="Candolle, A. P. de (1838) Prodromus systematis naturalis regni vegetabilis, vol. 7 (1). Treuttel &amp; Wurtz, Paris, 330 pp. [https: // www." type="book" year="1838">Candolle (1838: 148)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, comprised of eight species around 
<taxonomicName id="B0D34D05AD5DFFC1FB41FC098C72FC72" box="[1178,1313,915,940]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nigricans">
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FB41FC098C72FC72" box="[1178,1313,915,940]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">T. nigricans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Kitaibel in 
<bibRefCitation id="13424B77AD5DFFC1FF53FC2C880CFC0F" author="Schultes, J. A." box="[136,351,950,977]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" refId="ref4058" refString="Schultes, J. A. (1814) Osterreichs Flora, ed. 2, vol. 2. C. Schaumber &amp; Comp., Wien, 244 pp." type="book" year="1814">Schultes 1814: 405</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="13424B77AD5DFFC1FEB7FC2C8BDBFC0E" author="Reichenbach, H. G. L." box="[364,648,950,976]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" pagination="185 - 434" refId="ref3957" refString="Reichenbach, H. G. L. (1831) Flora germanica excursoria, vol. 1 (3). Carolum Cnobloch, Lipsiae, pp. 185 - 434." type="book chapter" year="1831">Reichenbach (1831: 270)</bibRefCitation>
, or the group of 
<taxonomicName id="B0D34D05AD5DFFC1FCE5FC2D8D96FC0E" authority="van Soest (1959: 134)" authorityName="van Soest" authorityPageNumber="134" authorityYear="1959" box="[830,1221,950,977]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhaeticum">
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FCE5FC2D8A9AFC0E" box="[830,969,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">T. rhaeticum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="13424B77AD5DFFC1FC14FC2D8D96FC0E" author="van Soest, J. L." box="[975,1221,950,977]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" pagination="77 - 138" refId="ref4344" refString="van Soest, J. L. (1959) Alpine species of Taraxacum. Acta Botanica Neerlandica 8: 77 - 138. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1438 - 8677.1959. tb 00013. x" type="journal article" year="1959">van Soest (1959: 134)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, or the group around 
<taxonomicName id="B0D34D05AD5DFFC1FF53FC418846FC2A" box="[136,277,986,1012]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reophilum">
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FF53FC418846FC2A" box="[136,277,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">T. reophilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, even when 
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FDCFFC418B7AFC2A" box="[532,553,987,1012]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">T.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FDB3FC408B9CFC2A" box="[616,719,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">Alpestria</emphasis>
would be understood as a narrow group of several species around 
<taxonomicName id="B0D34D05AD5DFFC1FF53FC658845FBC6" box="[136,278,1022,1048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reophilum">
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FF53FC658845FBC6" box="[136,278,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">T. reophilum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="B0D34D05AD5DFFC1FEFFFC658884FBC6" authorityName="Dahlstedt" authorityYear="1907" box="[292,471,1022,1048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rhodocarpum">
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FEFFFC658884FBC6" box="[292,471,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">T. rhodocarpum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be included in it.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3FC9650DAD5DFFC1FF66FBB88AF0F986" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" type="description">
<paragraph id="776C3686AD5DFFC1FF66FBB88B70FBBF" blockId="3.[136,1452,842,1625]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">
The following description emphasizes features shared by the majority of the members of 
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FB62FBB98D9DFBE2" box="[1209,1230,1059,1084]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">T.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FACAFBB88C2BFBE2" box="[1297,1400,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">Alpestria</emphasis>
, but covers also morphological extremes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="776C3686AD5DFFC1FF66FBF18AF0F986" blockId="3.[136,1452,842,1625]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FF66FBF18812FB5A" box="[189,321,1131,1156]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">Description</emphasis>
:—Plants medium-sized to ± robust; plant base without tunic. Leaves erect, erect-patent to ± patent, most often subglabrous to glabrous, usually deeply dissected, often having a shape of those of 
<taxonomicName id="B0D34D05AD5DFFC1FB0FFB158C0FFB76" box="[1236,1372,1166,1192]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Taraxacum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="officinale">
<emphasis id="45A7EA94AD5DFFC1FB0FFB158C0FFB76" box="[1236,1372,1166,1192]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="298">T. officinale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="5E9457EFAD5DFFC1FABDFB158CF4FB76" box="[1382,1447,1166,1193]" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" sensu="lato">s. lat.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, petiole often winged, or unwinged, mid-vein without the longitudinally striate pattern. Capitulum yellow, usually deep yellow or golden yellow, often large; stigmas discoloured, pollen usually present. Involucre medium broad, rounded to obconical at base, pruinose or not so. Outer phyllaries most often 12–19, ± appressed, loosely appressed, erectpatent, arcuate-patent to arcuate recurved, not tightly appressed, nor reflexed, usually from narrowly lanceolate to ovate-lanceolate, relatively short, most frequently (5–) 6–9 × 
<quantity id="B02B9B63AD5DFFC1FC9EFAD88AE9FA83" box="[837,954,1346,1373]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="2.75" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="2.0">2–3.5 mm</quantity>
, surface usually ± evenly olivaceous-green, dark olivaceous-green, deep grey-green, often blackish-green when dry, most often with an abrupt transition in an inconspicuous, membranous or whitish-membranous border 
<quantity id="B02B9B63AD5DFFC1FCECFA108A93FA7B" box="[823,960,1418,1445]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="0.2" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.1">0.1–0.3 mm</quantity>
wide, sometimes border absent or broader, margin glabrous or sparsely minutely ciliate, apex flat. Achenes light stramineous-brown, light yellowish brown, light greyish stramineous-brown, sometimes light brown to medium brown, or castaneous-brown or reddish brown, 3.5–5 × ca. 
<quantity id="B02B9B63AD5DFFC1FF17FA6C880BF9CF" box="[204,344,1526,1553]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.1" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="1.0" valueMax="1.1" valueMin="0.9">0.9–1.1 mm</quantity>
, achene body usually ± densely spinulose above, most often abruptly or subabruptly, seldom to gradually narrowing in a short subcylindrical to subconical, sometimes conical, cone usually 
<quantity id="B02B9B63AD5DFFC1FB47F9808C77F9EB" box="[1180,1316,1562,1589]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="298" unit="mm" value="0.7" valueMax="0.9" valueMin="0.5">0.5–0.9 mm</quantity>
long, rarely longer; beak thin, persistent, (4.5–) 6–8 (–9) mm long, pappus ± white.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
